channel.title: Croajingalong NP - Plants
channel.description: Including Mallacoota. Initial flora list supplied by Parks Victoria.

item.title: Cotula coronopifolia
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Taller than usual and with undivided leaves.

item.title: Polyscias sambucifolia subsp. 1
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Broadest leaves I've seen on this taxon.

item.title: Schoenus spp.
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Flowers on long stalks. Possibly S. brevifolius.

item.title: Comesperma defoliatum
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: About 50cm tall, leafless, often with just one flower.

item.title: Epacris paludosa
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: On the 2nd pic the glabrous style can be seen, which distinguishes it from the otherwise almost identical E. lanuginosa.

item.title: Blechnum minus
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Young plant - looks like a Pellaea but isn't.

item.title: Sannantha pluriflora
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: Used to be Baeckea virgata and has recently changed name again from Babingtonia pluriflora (via Babingtonia virgata) to Sannantha pluriflora!

item.title: Goodenia humilis
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: All plants here had red in upper petals. This occurs sometimes in G. humilis.

item.title: Candalides hyacinthina hyacinthina, Lobelia gibbosa s.s.
item.dc:creator: russell

item.title: Lobelia gibbosa s.s.
item.dc:creator: russell
item.description: First time I've been able to ID this species. Leaves not obviously lobed (so not L. dentata). Under the microscope, seed was 0.2-0.3mm long, reticulate, not 3-angled (so not L. simplicicaulis).
